==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fruitful
<hw>Fruit"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of fruit;
producing fruit abundantly; bearing results; prolific; fertile; liberal;
bountiful; <as>as, a <ex>fruitful</ex> tree, or season, or soil; a
<ex>fruitful</ex> wife.</as></def> -- <wordforms><wf>Fruit"ful*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> -- <wf>Fruit"ful*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Be <qex>fruitful</qex> and multiply and replenish the earth.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. i. 28.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Nature] By disburdening grows⟦br⟧
More <qex>fruitful</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The great <qex>fruitfulness</qex> of the poet's fancy.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Fertile; prolific; productive; fecund; plentiful;
rich; abundant; plenteous. See <er>Fertile</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fruiting</ent>⟦br⟧
